claim.claim-text:
1. An electric toothbrush comprising: 
a substantially hollow body having a head portion and a handle portion connected by a neck portion; 
a motor located within the handle portion; 
a first switch located within the handle portion having an open position and a closed position, wherein the open position prevents operation of the motor and the closed position facilitates automatic operation of the motor; 
a moveable brush head having a plurality of bristles; 
a drive assembly operatively connected between the motor and the moveable brush head; and 
a second switch located within the body, wherein actuating the second switch causes operation of the motor when the first switch is in the closed position, and wherein the second switch is automatically closed when the toothbrush is used by an operator.

11. An electric toothbrush comprising: 
a substantially hollow body having a head portion and a handle portion connected by a neck portion; 
a motor located within the handle portion; 
a first switch located within the handle portion having an open position, a first closed position and a second closed position, wherein the open position prevents operation of the motor, the first closed position facilitates automatic operation of the motor, and the second closed position causes the motor to operate continuously; 
a moveable brush head having a plurality of bristles; 
a drive assembly operatively connected between the motor and the moveable brush head; and 
a second switch located within the body, wherein actuating the second switch causes operation of the motor when the first switch is in the first closed position, and wherein the second switch is automatically closed when the tooth brush is used by an operator.
